The Independent Police Investigative Directorate has confirmed it is investigating a case of kidnapping. PRETORIA - Eyewitness News has learnt that South African Revenue Services (Sars) Commissioner Tom Moyane may face prosecution if it emerges he was issuing instructions for an employee to be held against his will. Several Hawks officials and Moyane's bodyguard are accused of holding Sars employee Vlok Symington hostage as they demanded he hand over a document apparently given to him in error. Police watchdog Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) has confirmed it is investigating a case of kidnapping. In a video recorded by Symington, Moyane's bodyguard can been seen talking on the phone while blocking the doorway. MUST WATCH: Hostage drama at Sars offices Advocate James Grant says if the guard was taking instructions from Moyane, he could be held liable. &quot;Whoever was on the other side of the phone was issuing instructions which destructions were causing the bodyguards to be interfering with the freedom of movement. Then that person will be held in law to have done whatever those bodyguards did.&quot; Sars says it is investigating the matter internally.